Executive Summary — Mars Dust Trap (Windcatcher)

The Mars Dust Trap is not a productivity system.
It is a risk-reduction and environment-conditioning asset.

Its value comes from:

reducing cumulative dust exposure to surface systems

slowing abrasion, fouling, and thermal/optical degradation

reducing maintenance frequency and intervention load

preventing secondary failures driven by dust accumulation

The system saves money by preventing expensive problems, not by “making new capability.”

Phase 3 Execution Path (License)
